## 9. UI/UX Design Direction

### Color Palette
| Role | Color | Hex |
|------|-------|-----|
| Primary (Trust Blue) | 🟦 | `#2563EB` |
| Accent (Action Orange) | 🟧 | `#F97316` |
| Success (Resolved Green) | 🟩 | `#10B981` |
| Danger (Critical Red) | 🟥 | `#EF4444` |
| Warning (Urgent Amber) | 🟨 | `#F59E0B` |
| Background (Dark) | ⬛ | `#0F172A` |
| Surface (Card) | ⬛ | `#1E293B` |
| Text Primary | ⬜ | `#F1F5F9` |

### Map Marker Color Coding
| Category | Marker Color | Icon |
|----------|-------------|------|
| Medical | 🔴 Red | ❤️‍🩹 |
| Food | 🟠 Orange | 🍚 |
| Shelter | 🔵 Blue | 🏠 |
| Rescue | 🟣 Purple | 🚨 |
| Education | 🟢 Green | 📚 |
| Clothing | 🟡 Yellow | 👕 |

### Design Principles
- **Dark mode by default** — professional, modern feel
- **Glassmorphism** cards — frosted glass effect on dashboard panels
- **Smooth animations** — Framer Motion for page transitions
- **Gradient accents** — subtle gradients on CTAs and headers
- **Micro-interactions** — hover effects on cards, pulse on urgent markers
- **Mobile-first** — responsive grid, touch-friendly map

