## 10. How We'll Implement This (Step-by-Step)

### 📁 Phase 1: Project Scaffolding (30 min)
1. Initialize React + Vite frontend in `/frontend`
2. Initialize FastAPI backend in `/backend`
3. Set up MongoDB connection (MongoDB Atlas free tier or local)
4. Create folder structure, install dependencies
5. Set up environment variables (`.env`)

### 🎨 Phase 2: Design System & Landing Page (1 hr)
1. Build `index.css` with CSS custom properties (colors, typography, spacing)
2. Import Google Font (Inter / Outfit)
3. Create the Landing Page with hero section, problem statement, and CTA
4. Build Navbar component with auth state

### 🔐 Phase 3: Authentication (1.5 hr)
1. Backend: User model, register/login endpoints, JWT middleware
2. Frontend: Login/Register page, AuthContext, protected routes
3. Two roles: `volunteer` and `admin`

### 📝 Phase 4: Need Reporting System (2 hr)
1. Backend: Need CRUD endpoints with geolocation
2. Frontend: Report Need form (category dropdown, urgency slider, location picker)
3. Integrate Leaflet mini-map for location selection
4. Wire up API calls

### 📷 Phase 5: OCR Integration (1.5 hr)
1. Build OCR Uploader component with Tesseract.js
2. Image upload → processing animation → extracted text display
3. Auto-fill form fields from extracted text
4. Demo with sample paper survey images

### 🗺️ Phase 6: Crisis Map Dashboard (2 hr)
1. Full-screen Leaflet map with OpenStreetMap tiles
2. Load all needs as markers (color-coded by category)
3. Marker popups with need details + "Assign Volunteer" button
4. Filter panel (category, urgency, status)
5. Cluster markers for dense areas (Leaflet.markercluster)

### 🧠 Phase 7: Smart Matching Engine (2 hr)
1. Backend: Implement the scoring algorithm
2. MongoDB geospatial queries ($near) for distance calculation
3. API: `/match/suggestions/:need_id` → returns top 5 ranked volunteers
4. Frontend: Match panel showing volunteer cards with score bars
5. Admin can approve/override matches

### 📊 Phase 8: Analytics & Polish (1.5 hr)
1. Summary stats cards (total needs, active volunteers, avg response time)
2. Category distribution bar chart
3. Urgency pie chart
4. Animate numbers with count-up effect

### 🧪 Phase 9: Testing & Demo Prep (1 hr)
1. Seed database with realistic demo data (20 needs, 15 volunteers)
2. Run through the full demo flow end-to-end
3. Fix edge cases and UI polish
4. Prepare demo script

